Blurb::
Choose how much each response is scaled
Description::
Each entry in
\c primary_scales may be a user-specified nonzero characteristic value
to be used in scaling each response. These values are
ignored for scaling type \c none, required for
\c value, and optional for \c log. If a single real
value is specified it will apply to each function. 

